The Chicago designer’s mission is to tell authentic stories through his work. On this collab, he tells his own—revisiting his artistic roots on the Chuck 70, Pro Leather and matching apparel and accessories.
 
The Chucks go back to where JFG got his start: bootleg graphic tees. Using t-shirt-like jersey material, Joe stitches together his history with a patchwork collage of old graphic-tee designs. The Pro Leather brings smooth retro finesse and disco vibes to the silhouette’s soulful legacy and showcases Joe’s expressive style. 
 
The full collection is available December 17 at 10am EST on Converse.com

As part of the Converse All Star Series, our ongoing experience for our global community to develop their voice and talents, last week All Stars had exclusive access to performances by @TaylorBennett and team members @Neemz16, from Boston, and London-based @DubiousFeux.⁣
⁣
Made for All Stars by All Stars, and powered by Converse’s creative network and collaborators, All Star Series manifests in a new content series of one-of-a-kind workshops, conversations and performances. ⁣
⁣
Check out the performances plus conversations with our All Stars at YouTube.com/Converse. #ConverseAllStars

We asked 15 All Stars to interpret the All Star manifesto which articulates the ambition of the Converse All Star community to serve as an engine for creative progress.
 
Next up is Princess Jiboye, @princessjiboye. She’s a spoken word artist out of South London by way of Nigeria. She’s telling stories set to beats about positivity, self-love and elevating silenced voices. Princess J highlights these issues because she believes everyone’s voice and everyone’s creativity is important—so much so it could even save a life. Princess J’s latest single, Big, is out now on all the streaming platforms.

Producer: @ishicamethrough
Mix & Master: @ishicamethrough
Cinematographers: @morenikejis.lens @elizabetholowu @princessjiboye
Editor: @princessjiboye

Introducing Converse Shapes, our new apparel essentials, inspired by body shape not gender.
 
Born from the belief that size is a reference point, not an identity, we condensed the 14 men’s and women’s sizes traditionally found in a collection to four. Our intelligent sizing uses radical pleats and gussets to create expansion, freedom and movement. 
 
Made from about 50% recycled cotton and about 50% virgin cotton, the collection was carefully crafted with a minimalist design approach.”
 
Gender free. Without traditional labels. Ready to be worn, your way. Converse Shapes Collection available now on Converse.com.

⁣
⁣
A year ago, Alexis Sablone worked with the Converse CONS design team to create a collection that paid tribute to Japanese design and the preparation she and other riders had taken on the road to Tokyo, where she hoped to be competing this summer.⁣⁣
⁣
Instead, like millions around the world, she has spent months in the confines of her home and neighborhood. In that time, she’s worked to further develop her creative production skills—concepting, self-shooting, self-editing, and mixing music—for the newest CONS collection aptly dubbed, Designed By Alexis.⁣⁣
⁣
The collection itself is an assortment of Alexis’ favorite Converse silhouettes: her AS One Star Pro, the Jack Purcell Pro, and the Louie Lopez Pro—a nod to her fellow CONS teammate.⁣⁣
⁣
Concepted and shot around Brooklyn, the video uses multi-angle shots to showcases the versatility of this creative, skater and the collection she designed—on and off the board. Check it out in full on IGTV and head to our stories to hear more about the process from @suminaynay herself.

This year we partnered with @Dazed to rethink the #Dazed100—looking at how it could evolve into more than a list of 100 creative visionaries, and instead use it as an opportunity to create change through their ideas.⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣
We asked everyone on the list a simple question: “What creative or philanthropic project could we support, to help you create tomorrow?,” and set up a dedicated fund to support selected projects and continue to spark progress.⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣
You voted for the ideas you wanted to see made reality with the fund, so now meet the eight recipients and learn more about their projects. #CreateTomorrow #ConverseAllStars

As part of the 2021 #OpenToChange initiative in partnership with @dazed, young designers, artists, filmmakers and changemakers from around the globe had the opportunity to be mentored by designer and Converse collaborator Samuel Ross (@design.by.samuelross). ⁣
⁣
For this first session he shared his inspiring advice on how to turn creativity into business success 💯⁣⁣
 ⁣⁣
Tap the 🔗 in our bio to watch the full session and stay tuned for more.

node.text:
Like his signature low top, CONS team rider @LouieLopez’s new Louie Lopez Pro Mid is a nod to Converse heritage and his Los Angeles roots. Louie’s vision was to turn his OG style into a mid top for stability with style 🛹⁣
⁣
“A mid felt like the perfect evolution of the low. I wanted something that would be complimentary to my low top but provided a different look and feel”.⁣

Using a premium suede rubber backed upper, cushy CX foam sock-liner, and grippy outsole, this new silhouette is made for skateboarding and his high bar in the streets.⁣

The Louie Lopez Pro Mid is available now on Converse.com — 🔗 in bio to shop. ⁣

node.text:
As we continue to spotlight All Star Projects, meet Jordan Anderson, the Converse All Star behind My Queer Blackness (@MQBMBQ), a digital platform seeking to broaden the narrative of the Black queer identity 👏⁣⁣⁣
 ⁣⁣⁣⁣
“Identity is a huge part of my work. I don’t like to think of identity as something that’s singular. I think identity is very plural in its essence. As a Black queer Jamaican, Italian by adoption, and so many other different things, these attributes contribute to who I am and contribute to what I do.”⁣⁣⁣⁣
 ⁣⁣⁣⁣
Born and raised in Jamaica and now living in Milan, Italy, Jordan began MQBMBQ this time last year. As BLM protests and fundraisers dominated global conversations, he noticed a lack of support for Black queer lives, even as hate crimes against Black trans women escalated. MQBMBQ began as a fundraiser to uplift this community and has since evolved into a space for continued collaboration with Black queer creatives from around the world 🚀⁣⁣⁣⁣
 ⁣⁣⁣⁣
To learn more about Jordan’s All Star Project, check out our stories. #ConverseAllStars

Introducing our first collaboration with Beijing streetwear brand SOULGOODS—inspired by their running concept “From Beijing to the World”, a campaign that aspires to share a slice of local culture with the world and shine a light on the bustling Beijing youth.
 
Their iconic “soul tiger” head logo takes over the Jack Purcell and Chuck 70 silhouettes, a design which represents the traditional Chinese cultural significance of transmitting positive energy to drive off evil spirits and invite good luck in 🐯
 
Every style has a meaning, every product has a story. Converse x @Soulgoods_Brand, available now on Converse.com.

Introducing Outer Voice Records, a South Asian American record label founded by Converse All Stars @jamesamathew and @phillymathew_ and launched through All Star Projects. They are an “all-Brown collective” that creates music to tell stories 💯⁣
 ⁣
“Our community does not lack talent, it lacks a platform.” Outer Voice strives to create that space, leveraging industry networks and successful mentors to help the best talent in the South Asian American community enter a hugely underrepresented industry 👏🏻
 ⁣
“The decision to have an all-South Asian team was a very easy one. We knew that if we were creating a label for South Asian Americans that it should also be by us, so that our experiences as a community in this country—specifically in the entertainment industry and in the music business—would be reflected at every stage and step of our label.”⁣
 ⁣
Visit @OuterVoiceRecords for the label's debut release 🎤 "Photographs", outervoicerecords.com for details on how to apply, and check out our stories to learn more about this crew and their inspiring mission. #ConverseAllStars

The Converse All Stars program is comprised of nearly 3,000 emerging creative leaders from over 30 countries across the globe, each changing the world in their own way through sustainability, diversity & inclusivity, and youth development (areas where progress is critically needed today).⁣⁣
 ⁣⁣
Within this program, we’re excited to announce All Star Projects—an ongoing initiative supporting the creative action of underrepresented All Star talent through funding and mentorship. Think: a South Asian American record label building a pipeline for their community to enter the industry or a digital platform sharing the stories of the LGBTQIA+ Black community in the fashion space. ⁣⁣
 ⁣⁣
With All Star Projects, we hope to break cultural barriers by establishing more opportunities for those creating next and to accelerate the impact of our All Star community 🌟⁣
⁣
Stay tuned for more. #ConverseAllStars 🎵: @kidbracer & @bapaksugi
